 is the form used in the Greek of the New Testament (Hebrews 11:11)."],"variants":[{"name":"Sarah","meanings":["Biblical name, borne by the wife of Abraham and mother of Isaac. According to the Book of Genesis, she was originally called <i>Sarai</i> (possibly meaning ‘contentious’ in Hebrew), but had her name changed by God to the more auspicious <i>Sarah</i> ‘princess’ in token of a greater blessing (Genesis 17:15, ‘And God said unto Abraham, As for Sarai thy wife, thou shalt not call her name Sarai, but Sarah shall her name be’). This has been one of the most enduringly popular girls' names."]}]},{"name":"verch","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Otto, Orlo.","German: variant of   Ferch  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Ferch","meanings":["German: variant of   Ferg  . Compare   Verch  .","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förtsch</b> (see   Foertsch  ).","Probably also an Americanized form of German <b>Förch</b> (see   Foerch  )."]}]},{"name":"Morgan","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Anglicized form of Welsh Morcant , traditionally a boy's name. In Britain since the late 1990s the name has become equally popular as a girl's name, perhaps adopted with conscious reference to  King Arthur's  jealous stepsister  Morgan le Fay . Elsewhere in the English-speaking world, especially in North America, where it also enjoys considerable popularity, it is used predominantly for girls."],"variants":[{"name":"Morcant","meanings":["Traditional: composed of an unexplained first element + a second representing the Old Celtic element <i>cant</i> ‘circle; completion’."]}]},{"name":"of","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Oswald   or any of the various other names beginning with <i>Os-</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Sara verch Morgan of Glamorgan was born about 1140, in Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom as the daughter of Morgan ap Meuric of Coity. She married Pagamus De Turberville. They were the parents of at least 7 sons. She died after 1177, in her hometown."},"et":{"Abt 1140–after 1177":"umbes 1140–pärast 1177","1140–1177":"1140–1177","1145–Female":"1145–Surnud","1140–1207":"1140–1207","1161–Male":"1161–Surnud","1169–Male":"1169–Surnud","1173–Male":"1173–Surnud","1175–Male":"1175–Surnud","1176–Male":"1176–Surnud","1177–Male":"1177–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1115–Male":"1115–Surnud","1176":"1176","1175":"1175","1173":"1173","1140":"1140","1161":"1161","Abt 1140":"umbes 1140","1115":"1115","1169":"1169","1145":"1145","1177":"1177","about 1169":"umbes 1169","after 1177":"pärast 1177","about 1177":"umbes 1177","1207":"1207","Coity Castle,Bridgend, Glamorgan, Wales":"Bridgend, Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom","Coity, Glamorgan, Wales":"Coity, Glamorgan, Wales","Crug Howall, Breconshire, Wales":"Breconshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1140–after 1177":"noin 1140–1177 jälkeen","1140–1177":"1140–1177","1145–Female":"1145–Kuollut","1140–1207":"1140–1207","1161–Male":"1161–Kuollut","1169–Male":"1169–Kuollut","1173–Male":"1173–Kuollut","1175–Male":"1175–Kuollut","1176–Male":"1176–Kuollut","1177–Male":"1177–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1115–Male":"1115–Kuollut","1176":"1176","1175":"1175","1173":"1173","1140":"1140","1161":"1161","Abt 1140":"noin 1140","1115":"1115","1169":"1169","1145":"1145","1177":"1177","about 1169":"noin 1169","after 1177":"1177 jälkeen","about 1177":"noin 1177","1207":"1207","Coity Castle,Bridgend, Glamorgan, Wales":"Bridgend, Glamorgan, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Coity, Glamorgan, Wales":"Coity, Glamorgan, Wales","Crug Howall, Breconshire, Wales":"Breconshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunt